      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the iconic 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant. This high-revving boxer engine utilizes VarioCam Plus timing and lift control, delivering linear power through a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut, benefitting from a factory-spec multi-link rear suspension and staggered 18-inch alloy wheels. Recent preventative maintenance includes an updated IMS bearing and a fresh clutch assembly, ensuring the longitudinal drivetrain remains robust. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the hydraulic power steering and four-piston Monobloc calipers provide the precise feedback and deceleration expected of a Zuffenhausen-engineered machine.",
      "price": 34500.0,
